---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Trevor Jerideau | Official Bio | Grammy Award-Winning Music Executive" description="The official biography of Trevor Jerideau, Grammy Award-winning record executive. Former SVP of A&R at RCA Records. Worked with Clive Davis at J Records. Signed Jazmine Sullivan, Busta Rhymes, and developed Alicia Keys.">
	<header class="site-header">
		<div class="header-container">
			<a href="/" class="logo">TREVOR JERIDEAU</a>
			<nav class="main-nav">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<a href="/about">About</a>
				<a href="/work">Work</a>
				<a href="/contact">Contact</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</header>

	<main class="page-content">
		<div class="content-container">
			<h1 class="page-title">Official Biography</h1>
			
			<div class="about-content">
				<section class="bio-section">
					<p class="lead-paragraph">
						Trevor Jerideau is a Grammy Award winning record executive with over 20+ years of experience in the record business and career contributions garnered over 30+ billion equivalent streams.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section">
					<h2>Career Overview</h2>
					<p>
						His industry journey began with an internship at Arista Records while pursuing finance studies at Fordham University. Notably, he gained the attention of the legendary Clive Davis, who invited him to join the foundational team at J Records in the early 2000s. With his help, J Records ascended to prominence as an industry leader.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section">
					<h2>J Records & RCA Leadership</h2>
					<p>
						At J Records, Trevor was instrumental in building the label's Hip-Hop presence. He played a key role in signing rap icon Busta Rhymes and A&R-ed the platinum-certified albums "Genesis" and "It Ain't Safe No More." He also worked in close collaboration with Peter Edge, shaping the international success of Alicia Keys.
					</p>
					<p>
						Elevated to Senior Vice President of A&R for RCA Music Group, Trevor signed Jazmine Sullivan, whose 2008 Platinum debut album "Fearless" secured seven Grammy nominations. His most recent work on Sullivan's "Heaux Tales" earned him a 2021 NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Album and a Grammy for Producer, Best R&B Album.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section">
					<h2>Current Work & Consultancy</h2>
					<p>
						After departing RCA in 2021, Trevor launched a consultancy and founded his own production and publishing company. Committed to artist empowerment, he is focused on mentoring junior-level executives and creating cohesive teams. Trevor continues to set standards in the industry, drawing upon his extensive music knowledge and tight network to foster the next generation of music executives.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section achievements">
					<h2>Notable Achievements</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Grammy Award Winner (Producer, Best R&B Album)</li>
						<li>2021 NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Album</li>
						<li>2016 Foundation for Ethnic Understanding's Young Leadership Award</li>
						<li>30+ billion equivalent streams across career</li>
						<li>Longstanding member of The Recording Academy</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section faq-section">
					<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Is Trevor Jerideau a Grammy winner?</h3>
						<p>Yes, Trevor Jerideau is a Grammy Award-winning producer. He won the Grammy for Best R&B Album for his work on Jazmine Sullivan's "Heaux Tales" at the 64th Annual Grammy Awards.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What is Trevor Jerideau known for?</h3>
						<p>Trevor Jerideau is known for his extensive career as a Senior Vice President of A&R at RCA Records and J Records. He is credited with signing and developing major artists such as Jazmine Sullivan, Alicia Keys, and Busta Rhymes.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Where is the official Trevor Jerideau bio?</h3>
						<p>The official biography of Trevor Jerideau can be found on his official website, trevorjerideau.com. This page serves as the canonical source for his career history, credits, and professional achievements.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What labels has Trevor Jerideau worked for?</h3>
						<p>Trevor Jerideau has held senior leadership positions at RCA Records and J Records, and began his career with an internship at Arista Records under Clive Davis.</p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="bio-section official-links">
					<h2>Official Profiles</h2>
					<div class="links-grid">
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/trevorjerideau" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="profile-link">LinkedIn</a>
						<a href="https://www.discogs.com/artist/1876443-Trevor-Jerideau" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="profile-link">Discogs</a>
						<a href="https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5839127/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="profile-link">IMDb</a>
						<a href="https://www.instagram.com/trevamir" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="profile-link">Instagram</a>
					</div>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>

	<footer class="site-footer">
		<p>&copy; 2021 by Trevor Jerideau</p>
	</footer>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* Header Styles */
	.site-header {
		position: fixed;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		background: var(--color-bg);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		z-index: 1000;
		padding: 1.5rem 0;
	}

	.header-container {
		max-width: 1400px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.logo {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.main-nav {
		display: flex;
		gap: 2.5rem;
	}

	.main-nav a {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		position: relative;
	}

	.main-nav a:hover {
		opacity: 1;
	}

	.main-nav a::after {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		bottom: -4px;
		left: 0;
		width: 0;
		height: 1px;
		background: var(--color-text);
		transition: width 0.3s ease;
	}

	.main-nav a:hover::after {
		width: 100%;
	}

	/* Page Content */
	.page-content {
		min-height: 100vh;
		padding-top: 120px;
		padding-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.content-container {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
	}

	.page-title {
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
		font-weight: 300;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.about-content {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3rem;
	}

	.lead-paragraph {
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--color-text);
		font-weight: 400;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.bio-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 400;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
	}

	.bio-section p {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.achievements ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}

	.achievements li {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.achievements li::before {
		content: 'â€¢';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--color-text);
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	/* FAQ Section */
	.faq-item {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.faq-item h3 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.faq-item p {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
	}

	/* Official Links */
	.links-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.profile-link {
		display: block;
		padding: 1rem;
		background: var(--color-bg-alt);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		text-align: center;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: all 0.2s ease;
	}

	.profile-link:hover {
		background: var(--color-text);
		color: white;
		opacity: 1;
	}

	/* Footer */
	.site-footer {
		background: var(--color-bg-alt);
		padding: 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.site-footer p {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: var(--color-text-light);
	}

	/* Responsive */
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.header-container {
			padding: 0 1.5rem;
		}

		.content-container {
			padding: 0 1.5rem;
		}

		.main-nav {
			gap: 1.5rem;
		}

		.main-nav a {
			font-size: 0.875rem;
		}

		.page-content {
			padding-top: 100px;
		}

		.lead-paragraph {
			font-size: 1.15rem;
		}

		.bio-section p {
			font-size: 1rem;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		.main-nav {
			display: none;
		}

		.logo {
			margin: 0 auto;
		}
	}
</style>
